</question>

<!-- Q3 -->
<question type="multichoice">
  <name><text>Wald - Var(S_N), N~Geom(1/3), Xi~Uniform[0,2]</text></name>
  <questiontext format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p>Let \(N\) be Geometric with \(P(N=k)=\left(\tfrac{2}{3}\right)^{k-1}\!\tfrac{1}{3}\), \(k\ge1\), and \(X_i\overset{iid}{\sim}\mathrm{Uniform}[0,2]\), independent of \(N\). Then \(\mathrm{Var}(X_1+\cdots+X_N)\) equals:</p>]]></text></questiontext>
  <generalfeedback format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Answer: (B) \(7\)</strong></p><p>For Geom\((p=1/3)\): \(E[N]=3\), \(\mathrm{Var}(N)=\tfrac{1-p}{p^2}=6\). For \(X\sim U[0,2]\): \(E[X]=1\), \(\mathrm{Var}(X)=\tfrac{1}{3}\). Wald: \(\mathrm{Var}(S)=3\cdot\tfrac{1}{3}+1^2\cdot6=1+6=7\).</p>]]></text></generalfeedback>
