<!-- Q14 -->
<question type="multichoice">
  <name><text>Wald - MGF of Compound Poisson Sum</text></name>
  <questiontext format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p>Let \(N\sim\mathrm{Poisson}(\lambda)\) and \(X_i\) i.i.d. with moment generating function \(M_X(t)\), independent of \(N\). The MGF of \(S=X_1+\cdots+X_N\) is:</p>]]></text></questiontext>
  <generalfeedback format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Answer: (C) \(\exp\!\left(\lambda(M_X(t)-1)\right)\)</strong></p><p>By iterated expectation: \(M_S(t)=E[e^{tS}]=E[E[e^{tS}|N]]=E[M_X(t)^N]=\sum_{n=0}^\infty M_X(t)^n\frac{e^{-\lambda}\lambda^n}{n!}=e^{-\lambda}e^{\lambda M_X(t)}=e^{\lambda(M_X(t)-1)}\).</p>]]></text></generalfeedback>
  <defaultgrade>1.0</defaultgrade><penalty>0.25</penalty><hidden>0</hidden>
  <single>true</single><shuffleanswers>true</shuffleanswers><answernumbering>abc</answernumbering>
  <answer fraction="0" format="html"><text>\(\lambda M_X(t)\)</text><feedback format="html"><text></text></feedback></answer>
  <answer fraction="0" format="html"><text>\(e^{-\lambda}M_X(t)\)</text><feedback format="html"><text></text></feedback></answer>
  <answer fraction="100" format="html"><text>\(\exp(\lambda(M_X(t)-1))\)</text><feedback format="html"><text></text></feedback></answer>
  <answer fraction="0" format="html"><text>\(e^{\lambda M_X(t)}\)</text><feedback format="html"><text></text></feedback></answer>
</question>

