<!-- Q16 -->
<question type="multichoice">
  <name><text>Wald - Sequential Testing Expected Sample Size</text></name>
  <questiontext format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p>In a sequential experiment, \(X_i\overset{iid}{\sim}\mathrm{Bernoulli}(p)\) and sampling stops at \(N=\min\{n:X_1+\cdots+X_n=k\}\). By Wald's identity \(E[S_N]=p\cdot E[N]\). Since \(E[S_N]=k\), the expected stopping time \(E[N]\) is:</p>]]></text></questiontext>
  <generalfeedback format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Answer: (B) \(k/p\)</strong></p><p>Wald: \(k=E[S_N]=p\cdot E[N]\Rightarrow E[N]=k/p\). This is the expected number of Bernoulli trials to achieve \(k\) successes — consistent with the negative binomial expectation.</p>]]></text></generalfeedback>
