  <answer fraction="0" format="html"><text>\(k(1-p)\)</text><feedback format="html"><text></text></feedback></answer>
  <answer fraction="0" format="html"><text>\(k/p^2\)</text><feedback format="html"><text></text></feedback></answer>
</question>

<!-- Q17 -->
<question type="multichoice">
  <name><text>Wald - Conditional E[S|N=n]</text></name>
  <questiontext format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p>Let \(N\) be a random variable and \(X_i\) i.i.d. with mean \(\mu\), independent of \(N\). Then \(E[X_1+\cdots+X_N \mid N=n]\) equals:</p>]]></text></questiontext>
  <generalfeedback format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Answer: (A) \(n\mu\)</strong></p><p>Given \(N=n\), the sum \(S_N=X_1+\cdots+X_n\) is fixed-size, so \(E[S_N|N=n]=n\mu\) by linearity. Taking expectation over \(N\) then gives \(E[S_N]=E[N]\mu\) — Wald's identity.</p>]]></text></generalfeedback>
  <defaultgrade>1.0</defaultgrade><penalty>0.25</penalty><hidden>0</hidden>
