<question type="multichoice">
  <name><text>Wald - Random Walk First Passage Expected Time</text></name>
  <questiontext format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p>Let \(X_i\overset{iid}{\sim}\) distribution with \(E[X_i]=\mu>0\). Let \(\tau=\min\{n:X_1+\cdots+X_n>a\}\) for some \(a>0\). Neglecting overshoots, Wald's identity suggests \(E[\tau]\approx\):</p>]]></text></questiontext>
  <generalfeedback format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Answer: (C) \(a/\mu\)</strong></p><p>By Wald's identity: \(E[S_\tau]=\mu\cdot E[\tau]\approx a\) (ignoring overshoot beyond \(a\)). Thus \(E[\tau]\approx a/\mu\). This approximation is exact for renewal theory in many cases.</p>]]></text></generalfeedback>
