<question type="multichoice">
  <name><text>Wald - Compound Poisson Insurance Model</text></name>
  <questiontext format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p>In a collective risk model, claims arrive as \(N\sim\mathrm{Poisson}(10)\) per year and individual claim amounts \(X_i\) are i.i.d. with \(E[X_i]=500\) and \(\mathrm{Var}(X_i)=90000\). The variance of total annual claim \(S=X_1+\cdots+X_N\) is:</p>]]></text></questiontext>
  <generalfeedback format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Answer: (D) \(3{,}400{,}000\)</strong></p><p>Compound Poisson: \(\mathrm{Var}(S)=\lambda E[X^2]=\lambda(\mathrm{Var}(X)+(E[X])^2)=10(90000+250000)=10\times340000=3{,}400{,}000\). Alternatively: \(E[N]\mathrm{Var}(X)+\mathrm{Var}(N)(E[X])^2=10\times90000+10\times250000=3{,}400{,}000\).</p>]]></text></generalfeedback>
